    RimWorld-style worldbuilding: a fractured human civilization scattered across the edge of known space. On lawless rimworlds far from central authority, vast and dangerous planets force survivors to rely on themselves. Without faster-than-light travel or communication, worlds remain isolated and unevenly developed, allowing primitive tribes, industrial societies, high-tech factions, and near-godlike machines to coexist. The tone blends hard sci-fi with frontier survival, focusing on ordinary people enduring and creating stories in a broken world.
    
